  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1985-05-22", 
    "text": "Juvenile Detention Employees Clearance Act of 1985 - Prohibits the employment of any person at a facility maintained for the detention, correction, care, or treatment of juveniles unless a nationwide criminal record check has ascertained whether such person poses a significant danger of abuse or mistreatment of the juveniles. Directs the Attorney General to assist State governments in their investigations."
